@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About - URL Shortener Algorithm</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container mt-5">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-4">About the URL Shortening Algorithm</h1>

        <div class="card shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h3 class="card-title">Algorithm Description</h3>
                <p class="card-text">
                    Our URL shortening algorithm is designed to take a long URL and convert it into a shorter, more manageable version.
                    This shorter URL can be used to quickly redirect users to the original address.
                </p>
                <h5>How the Algorithm Works:</h5>
                <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-3">
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        The user provides a long URL they wish to shorten.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        The algorithm generates a unique identifier for the URL using a random 5 letters.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        The original URL and its shortened version are stored in the database for future lookup.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        When a user accesses the shortened URL, the system looks up the original URL in the database and redirects the user to the target website.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
</body>
